U.N. Chief Targets 'Dangerous Epidemic Of Misinformation' On CoronavirusEnlarge this image toggle caption Juan Karita/AP Juan Karita/APThe world is facing "a dangerous epidemic of misinformation" about COVID-19 — and the only vaccine is to reestablish public trust, the head of the United Nations said Tuesday.
They want to know what to do and where to turn for advice," said U.N. Secretary-General António Guterres.
"This is a time for science and solidarity," Guterres said in a video message about his plan.
"First, trust in science," Guterres said, adding, "I salute the journalists and others fact-checking the mountain of misleading stories and social media posts."
The U.N. head called on social media companies to do more to root out harmful and bogus claims about COVID-19.